<p><b>Simone Weil</b> (<small>IPA</small>:&#160;<span title="Pronunciation in IPA" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA" title="Wikipedia:IPA">[simɔn vɛj]</a></span>; 3 February 1909 in Paris, France – 24 August 1943 in <a href="/wiki/Ashford,_Kent" title="Ashford, Kent">Ashford, Kent</a>, England), who occasionally used the <a href="/wiki/Anagram" title="Anagram">anagrammatic</a> <a href="/wiki/Pen_name" title="Pen name">pen name</a> Emile Novis, was a French <a href="/wiki/Philosopher" title="Philosopher" class="mw-redirect">philosopher</a>, <a href="/wiki/Christian_mysticism" title="Christian mysticism">Christian mystic</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Social_activist" title="Social activist" class="mw-redirect">social activist</a>.</p>
